Ladies and Gentleman please enjoy this melodious sung polka called "Man is Blind", by the one and only Carl Michael Ziehrer. 

Ziehrer's fiancée, Marianne Edelmann, conduceted this polka at a charity evening on august 27, 1882 at their engagement party in St. Petersburg. The success was overwherlming, and the printing of this piece was a box office hit. Ziehrer had composed a series of cheerful songs and couplets (op. 227 to op. 331a) for his Marianne. They were all, with a single exception played that night.

